1
00:00:04,662 --> 00:00:09,901
If we think of what Narada told Vyas,

2
00:00:09,901 --> 00:00:14,089
then we'll get a hint of how to interpret what is there.

3
00:00:14,336 --> 00:00:17,793
Absolute Good Breaking Bad

4
00:00:18,100 --> 00:00:21,177
And one thing we're told, he said,

5
00:00:21,869 --> 00:00:27,090
in the jugupsitam dharma-krte anusasanah sloka

6
00:00:27,906 --> 00:00:38,389
that he condemned mundane religion.

7
00:00:42,018 --> 00:00:45,582
Guru Maharaj paraphrased in this way

8
00:00:45,582 --> 00:00:56,843
by saying "You've told people how to get free from their disease,

9
00:00:56,843 --> 00:01:01,168
but you didn't tell them about a healthy life.'

10
00:01:04,061 --> 00:01:08,360
Because the emphasis is on - here's the disease, how to treat the disease,

11
00:01:08,360 --> 00:01:12,647
how to come to the healthy position.

12
00:01:12,893 --> 00:01:16,178
But the positive aspects about healthy life,

13
00:01:16,209 --> 00:01:19,321
that, he did not properly indicate.

14
00:01:19,767 --> 00:01:23,380
He said "You've done a great disservice

15
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:31,093
by indirectly promoting mundane religion",

16
00:01:31,601 --> 00:01:39,660
religion meaning religion followed to live happily in the mundane world.

17
00:01:42,183 --> 00:01:48,829
Not with the target of entry into the positive, serving, spiritual domain.

18
00:01:50,813 --> 00:01:53,859
So he used the word jugupsitam,

19
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:56,825
it means: condemned.

20
00:01:57,194 --> 00:01:58,727
Sometimes Guru Maharaj would say

21
00:01:58,727 --> 00:02:01,941
"Traitor, treacheror, you're a traitor to the cause."

22
00:02:01,941 --> 00:02:05,191
Narada's chastising him very severely.

23
00:02:06,406 --> 00:02:10,191
But after we hear the passtimes of Krishna

24
00:02:10,191 --> 00:02:12,031
with Radharani and Braja gopis,

25
00:02:13,845 --> 00:02:19,300
when Pariksit Maharaj sees the apprehensive look

26
00:02:19,300 --> 00:02:22,660
on the faces of the sages assembled there,

27
00:02:23,075 --> 00:02:25,745
he again uses the word jugupsitam

28
00:02:25,745 --> 00:02:32,100
and says, "In the beginning, Narada was chastising Vyas

29
00:02:32,100 --> 00:02:39,277
for, in a sense, giving religion -

30
00:02:39,938 --> 00:02:42,092
as it was understood up to that point -

31
00:02:42,831 --> 00:02:44,429
that it would mislead people.

32
00:02:44,429 --> 00:02:50,942
Now.. and you're saying, now the dharmic dharma projita kaitava,

33
00:02:50,942 --> 00:02:53,793
the purest thing, is going to be given,

34
00:02:53,793 --> 00:02:56,126
and what did you just tell everyone?

35
00:02:56,126 --> 00:03:00,936
That not only is Krishna aprakrita lila,

36
00:03:01,183 --> 00:03:05,626
krsnera yateka khela, sarvottama nara-lila,
nara-vapu tahara svarupa,

37
00:03:05,626 --> 00:03:08,820
a man, human like passtimes,

38
00:03:08,820 --> 00:03:12,824
but now you're telling us he's an immoral man.

39
00:03:13,548 --> 00:03:18,670
So people who are moral and follow religion -

40
00:03:21,530 --> 00:03:23,859
that's to be rejected,

41
00:03:23,859 --> 00:03:27,830
and here's Krishna, violating the principals of religion,

42
00:03:27,999 --> 00:03:31,233
we're supposed to understand 'this is the highest thing'.

43
00:03:32,156 --> 00:03:36,982
Very interesting new religion you're presenting here.

44
00:03:36,982 --> 00:03:40,419
So following moral principals: bad.

45
00:03:40,419 --> 00:03:43,752
Breaking all these principals: good.

46
00:03:44,783 --> 00:03:53,371
Well, yes, when you're - if you're - the abosolute good, yes.

47
00:03:53,833 --> 00:04:00,376
Then your stealing is worshipable,

48
00:04:00,623 --> 00:04:05,461
your seeming encroachment upon the properties of others

49
00:04:05,461 --> 00:04:07,841
is a delight.

